- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a framework for families of Turing complete stochastic languages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses exact inference algorithms for recursive stochastic languages, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses computational complexity costs and efficient computation, which are topics related to information theory. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of computational techniques for recursive stochastic languages, which can be applied in control systems.
